author: Ural Garrett
title: Birdman Dropping 500 Unreleased Cash Money Tracks By The End Of 2017?
text:
5 
Beyond his public rift with Lil Wayne and last year’s controversial moment with The Breakfast Club, Birdman has been fairly quiet on the music side of things. More notably, there hasn’t been much news on Cash Money’s future outside of known releases from Drake and Nicki Minaj. 
Though the question of whether or not Tha Carter V will drop remains to be unanswered (unless you ask Martin Shkreli) , Baby looks to drop some unreleased music from the legendary New Orleans label soon, according to a recent Instagram post. 
“Wen in my VAULT today found thousands of OLD CASHMONEY MUSIC will release 500 songs this Year #CASHMONEY COLLECTION,” the caption says. 
Throughout the company’s over 20-year history, numerous artists have come and gone. Does this mean we could hear more pre-internet fame Weezy or pre-breakup The Hot Boys? Who knows?
